Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 13.12.2024
Commitment to Privacy
Welcome to Rouvy.com and related applications ROUVY Desktop, Mobile and Tablet application, PowerTap Mobile, Magura Mobile, O-Synce Mobile, Bulls Mobile  – (collectively “ROUVY,” “We,” “Us,” or “Our”).
VirtualTraining s.r.o. is the creator of the ROUVY application (hereinafter in some parts of these principles, we use the name Rouvy also to refer to VirtualTraining s.r.o.). The VirtualTraining s.r.o. team sees its mission in simulating outdoor cycling routes and enabling competitions and training on cycling trainers on these routes. This makes competitions and training more engaging and productive. The Rouvy product aims to become a central application that aggregates all year-round training data from the cycling simulator.
We respect your right to privacy. Your ability to make informed choices about the use of your information is important to us. We want to make sure that you understand the type of information we collect about you, how it is used and the safeguards we use to protect it. This Privacy Policy explains our policy regarding the collection, use, disclosure and protection of personal information you share with us.
Before you get to the details, here are a few of our fundamental privacy principles:
Information you upload or post to ROUVY may be seen by others depending on your privacy settings.
We aggregate and de-identify certain information about our members to use for business purposes.
We give you several ways to control the privacy of your personal information and are continuously working to enhance privacy options available to you.
Please also read the Terms of Use which sets out the terms governing ROUVY and the ROUVY Legal Cookie Statement.
