Consent to Personal Data Processing (EU customers)
What is consent to personal data processing?
Consent to personal data processing is a freely given, specific, informed and unambiguous indication of consent you, as a data subject, grant to the processing of your personal data by a making statement or taking a clear confirmatory action to that effect. Consent is an active, voluntary expression of your intent, which you must not be forced to grant.
Consent to personal data processing is one of the legal reasons based on which we are allowed to process your personal data. Consent is required in every case where the reason for processing cannot be classified under the purposes for which the grant of consent is not required.
You may revoke your consent. The revocation of your consent does not necessarily require us to delete your personal data because the revocation of consent pertains to a specific purpose for which personal data are processed, and we might be processing your personal data for other purposes on legal grounds that differ from personal data processing to which you have granted consent. We are required to stop processing your personal data only if your consent constitutes the sole legal grounds for personal data processing.
Your consent to personal data processing is not required for processing your personal data in the following cases:
processing your personal data is necessary for performing an agreement to which VirtualTraining s.r.o. is a party as the controller of personal data, or for adopting measures at the request of the relevant data subject prior to entering into an agreement,
processing is necessary for complying with a legal obligation to which VirtualTraining s.r.o. is subject,
processing your personal data is necessary for protecting your vital interests as a data subject or the vital interests of another person,
processing your personal data is necessary for performing a task carried out in public interest or as part of the exercise of official authority wherewith may be vested the controller of personal data,
processing is necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests of the controller or a third party, except where such interests are overridden by the interests or fundamental rights and freedoms of the data subject whose personal data require protection.
You have the right to revoke your consent to personal data processing at any time.
Protection of Personal Data of Children
If you are a parent or the legal guardian of a child and you want to open a ROUVY account for your child, read carefully this section of the personal data processing policy.
If you believe that a child, aged below 13 years (USA) or 16 years (EEA) or below the age at which the law of the state where the child resides restricts independent juridical acts in relation to services corresponding to services provided by the ROUVY application has provided personal data without parental consent, contact us at gdpr@rouvy.com. We will make maximum effort to remove such personal data from our files as soon as possible.
In opening an account for your child, we will ask you to create a user name for your child (choose a name unrelated to your child’s real name) and to provide your child's personal data, such as his/her email address that will serve for sign-in purposes. In addition, we will require your name, surname, relationship to the child (parent or legal guardian), and e-mail address. Kindly note that the e-mail address provided for the purpose of signing in to your child's account must not be associated with an existing ROUVY membership. You or your child will be asked about your child's sex, height, and weight to allow us to calculate training data accurately. In addition, we will collect all information provided by you or by your child for the purposes of adapting your child's profile.
When ROUVY services are used by your child, we collect training data, including the route, pedalling frequency, effort, trip length, overall performance, total calories burned, elevation, and heart rate, provided that your child uses a heart rate sensor. In addition, we collect information on all screenshots taken by your child, completed challenges and missions, your child's experience level, and test results.
Information we collect is used to provide, adapt, and improve our services, to perform user identification, to monitor activities and training, and to provide customer support. In addition, collected data are used for internal purposes, such as troubleshooting, error protection, data analysis and testing, development of new functions and services, and improvement of the safety and security of ROUVY services.
No data relating to ROUVY child accounts are shared, sold, or disclosed to third parties with the exception of the following situations:
we provide personal data to service providers for data processing based on our instructions, subject to compliance with relevant appropriate measures ensuring confidentiality and security,
if we take part in a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, we will continue adopting measures protecting the confidentiality of personal data, and you will be notified before personal data are handed over to the successor company; likewise, we will ensure that your child's personal data remain protected by the legal successor in a situation resulting from any of the abovementioned transactions.
We have the right to disclose your child's personal data if required to comply with laws, regulations, legal procedures, requests made by government authorities, to exercise our legal rights, to defend ourselves against legal claims, and to protect ourselves from unlawful acts.
Being the parent or legal guardian, you have control over your child’s account and you have access to the account. That includes the right to make changes concerning the account.
If you want to stop the further collection or use of information relating to your child, you can revoke your data collection consent by sending an e-mail to gdpr@rouvy.com.
Links To Other Companies
Periodically, ROUVY may contain links to and from websites of our business partners, distributors, resellers, advertisers or other third parties. If you follow a link to any of these websites, please note that these websites have their own privacy policies which you should read before you submit any personal data to these websites. We disclaim any liability for the data processing activities of our business partners, distributors and resellers, all of which act as independent data processing controllers.
Co-Branded Websites
We also link to co-branded websites that are maintained by ROUVY and one or more of our business partners. An example of a co-branded website is the ROUVY e-shop. When you submit information to one of our co-branded websites, you may be submitting it to both ROUVY and our business partners. Please note that the privacy policies of these co-branded websites may differ from this Privacy Policy. We encourage you to read the privacy policies on any co-branded website to which you link, and we disclaim any liability for the data processing activities of our business partners which act as independent data processing controllers.
Discussion Groups and Forums
Please remember that information you submit in a discussion group or forum at ROUVY will be deemed public information and is not confidential. There is a risk in such communication venues that various information and data can be collected and used by others. Please be careful and responsible when you are on-line.
Participation in competitions and other organized or co-organized ROUVY events (by VirtualTraining s.r.o.)
By completing and submitting the competition form, the competition participant expresses his/her agreement with the terms of the competition and agrees that the company VirtualTraining s.r.o. will process his/her personal data necessary for participation in the competition up to the extent set forth above in this Policy (hereinafter referred to as "personal data").
The purpose of personal data processing is the organization and management of the VirtualTraining s.r.o. competition, including announcement of the results to the competition participant, information about potential awards in the competition and publication of the competitor's personal data in the media or on the Internet, as well as for the marketing purposes of the administrator and its business partners, i.e. offering of products and services and sending information about the marketing events of these subjects to the competition participant. The provision of personal data and its processing is based on the legitimate interest of VirtualTraining s.r.o. and is necessary for the realization of the competition and the participation of the participant in it, as well as for the fulfillment of the marketing interests of the organizer’s business partners who offer their products and services.
VirtualTraining s.r.o. as the administrator of the personal data, will not share the personal data with any third parties, with the exception of the administrator's business partners, who may use the personal data to contact the participants for the purpose of offering products and services produced by those business partners.
Personal data of the competition participants will be stored and processed for the period necessary for the purpose of processing, but no longer than for a period of 10 years from the last day on which the competition takes place.
Legal rules governing each competition and all relations resulting from it, including the personal data processing are governed by the jurisdiction of the Czech Republic and in connection with the provision of personal data, the competition participant has rights in accordance with Regulation of the European Parliament and the Council (EU) no. 2016/679 of April 27, 2016, general regulation on personal data protection, in particular: a. the right to access personal data; b. the right to correct inaccurate or incomplete personal data; c. the right to erase personal data; d. the right to limit the processing of personal data; e. the right to personal data transfer; and f. the right to contact the Office for Personal Data Protection (www.uoou.cz) if the competition participant believes that his/her personal data is not handled in compliance with legal rules. See other sections of this Policy for more details.
